SIMPLE: oosphere
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oosphere
<hw>O"o*sphere</hw> <pr>(⟦omac⟧"⟦osl⟧*sf⟦emac⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>w,'o`n</grk> an egg + E. <ets>sphere</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An unfertilized, rounded mass of
protoplasm, produced in an oogonium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ After being fertilized by the access of antherozoids it
becomes covered with a cell wall and develops into an oospore, which may
grow into a new plant like the parent.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An analogous mass of protoplasm in
the ovule of a flowering plant; an embryonic vesicle.</def>
<rj><au>Goodale.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oosporangium</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
